# Performance Standards

## Bundle Optimization

Keep bundle size minimal:

### 1. Tree Shaking

Use named exports for tree shaking:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - tree shaking friendly
export { Button } from './Button';
export { Input } from './Input';
export { Modal } from './Modal';

// ❌ Bad - not tree shaking friendly
export default { Button, Input, Modal };
```

### 2. Lazy Loading

Implement lazy loading for heavy components:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - lazy loading
const HeavyComponent = lazy(() => import('./HeavyComponent'));

const App = () => (
  <Suspense fallback={<Spinner />}>
    <HeavyComponent />
  </Suspense>
);
```

### 3. Dynamic Imports

Use dynamic imports for non-critical code:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - dynamic import
const loadChart = async () => {
  const { Chart } = await import('./Chart');
  return Chart;
};
```

## Rendering Optimization

### 1. React.memo

Use React.memo for expensive components:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - memo for expensive components
export const ExpensiveComponent = React.memo<ExpensiveComponentProps>(
  ({ data, onUpdate }) => {
    // Component implementation
  },
  (prevProps, nextProps) => {
    // Custom comparison if needed
    return prevProps.data.id === nextProps.data.id;
  },
);
```

### 2. useCallback

Use useCallback for event handlers:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - useCallback for handlers
const Button = ({ onClick, children }: ButtonProps) => {
  const handleClick = useCallback((event: React.MouseEvent) => {
    onClick?.(event);
  }, [onClick]);

  return <button onClick={handleClick}>{children}</button>;
};
```

### 3. useMemo

Use useMemo for expensive calculations:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - useMemo for expensive calculations
const DataTable = ({ data, filters }: DataTableProps) => {
  const filteredData = useMemo(() => {
    return data.filter(item =>
      filters.every(filter => filter.predicate(item))
    );
  }, [data, filters]);

  return <table>{/* render filtered data */}</table>;
};
```

### 4. Avoid Unnecessary Re-renders

Optimize props to avoid re-renders:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - stable props
const ParentComponent = () => {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  // Create stable object
  const config = useMemo(() => ({
    theme: 'dark',
    size: 'large'
  }), []);

  return <ChildComponent config={config} />;
};

// ❌ Bad - object recreated on each render
const ParentComponent = () => {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return <ChildComponent config={{ theme: 'dark', size: 'large' }} />;
};
```

## Image Optimization

### 1. Lazy Loading Images

```typescript
const LazyImage = ({ src, alt, ...props }: ImageProps) => {
  const [isLoaded, setIsLoaded] = useState(false);
  const [isInView, setIsInView] = useState(false);
  const imgRef = useRef<HTMLImageElement>(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      ([entry]) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          setIsInView(true);
          observer.disconnect();
        }
      },
      { threshold: 0.1 }
    );

    if (imgRef.current) {
      observer.observe(imgRef.current);
    }

    return () => observer.disconnect();
  }, []);

  return (
    <div ref={imgRef} className="image-container">
      {isInView && (
        <img
          src={src}
          alt={alt}
          onLoad={() => setIsLoaded(true)}
          className={isLoaded ? 'loaded' : 'loading'}
          {...props}
        />
      )}
    </div>
  );
};
```

### 2. SVG Optimization

```typescript
// ✅ Good - optimized SVG
const Icon = ({ name, size = 24 }: IconProps) => {
  const iconPath = useMemo(() => getIconPath(name), [name]);

  return (
    <svg
      width={size}
      height={size}
      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
      fill="currentColor"
      aria-hidden="true"
    >
      <path d={iconPath} />
    </svg>
  );
};
```

## State Optimization

### 1. Local vs Global State

Use local state when possible:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - local state
const Button = ({ $loading: initialLoading = false }: ButtonProps) => {
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(initialLoading);

  const handleClick = async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    try {
      await performAction();
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };

  return <button disabled={loading} onClick={handleClick}>Click</button>;
};
```

### 2. Context Optimization

Optimize Context to avoid re-renders:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - optimized Context
const ThemeContext = createContext<ThemeContextValue | null>(null);

const ThemeProvider = ({ children }: ThemeProviderProps) => {
  const [theme, setTheme] = useState('light');

  const value = useMemo(() => ({
    theme,
    setTheme,
    isDark: theme === 'dark'
  }), [theme]);

  return (
    <ThemeContext.Provider value={value}>
      {children}
    </ThemeContext.Provider>
  );
};
```

## CSS Optimization

### 1. Design Tokens Performance (PRIORITY)

Use design tokens from `/packages/react/src/styles/` for optimal performance:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - using design tokens for stable styles
const Button = ({ $variant, $size, children }: ButtonProps) => {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        // Using design system tokens (PRIORITY)
        'typo-body-2-emphasized whitespace-nowrap rounded-x2',
        'flex items-center justify-center w-fit',
        'disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:cursor-not-allowed',
        // Variants using design tokens
        buttonVariants({ $variant, $size })
      )}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};

// ❌ Bad - expensive dynamic styles
const Button = ({ $variant }: ButtonProps) => {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        // Don't use hardcoded values
        'text-sm font-medium rounded-md px-4 py-2',
        $variant === 'primary' ? 'bg-blue-500 text-white' : 'bg-gray-200 text-gray-900'
      )}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

### 2. Critical CSS with Design Tokens (PRIORITY)

Prioritize critical CSS using design tokens from `/packages/react/src/styles/`:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - critical CSS first with design tokens
const Button = ({ $variant, $size, children }: ButtonProps) => {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        // Critical base styles using design tokens (PRIORITY)
        'typo-body-2-emphasized whitespace-nowrap rounded-x2',
        'flex items-center justify-center w-fit',
        'disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:cursor-not-allowed',
        // Focus states using design tokens
        'focus-visible:!outline-[2px] focus-visible:!outline-offset-2 focus-visible:!outline-stroke-brand',
        // Variants using design tokens
        buttonVariants({ $variant, $size })
      )}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

## Monitoring and Profiling

### 1. Performance Monitoring

```typescript
// ✅ Good - performance monitoring
const usePerformanceMonitor = (componentName: string) => {
  useEffect(() => {
    const startTime = performance.now();

    return () => {
      const endTime = performance.now();
      console.log(`${componentName} render time: ${endTime - startTime}ms`);
    };
  });
};
```

### 2. Bundle Analysis

Use the existing analysis tools in the project:

```bash
# Analyze bundle size (available in packages/react)
pnpm analyze

# Build with analysis (available in packages/react)
pnpm run analyze

# Run analysis for all packages
pnpm run analyze
```

## Performance Checklist

### Bundle Optimization

- [ ] Bundle size < 50KB gzipped (use `pnpm analyze` to check)
- [ ] Tree shaking working (use named exports)
- [ ] No unused dependencies
- [ ] Design tokens used instead of hardcoded values

### Rendering Performance

- [ ] React.memo used for expensive components
- [ ] useCallback used for event handlers
- [ ] useMemo used for expensive calculations
- [ ] No unnecessary re-renders
- [ ] Stable props passed to children

### CSS Performance

- [ ] Design tokens used from `/packages/react/src/styles/`
- [ ] No hardcoded colors, spacing, or typography
- [ ] Critical CSS prioritized
- [ ] No expensive dynamic styles

### Testing Performance

- [ ] Use `pnpm test:coverage` to check test coverage
- [ ] Use `pnpm test:run` for performance testing
- [ ] No memory leaks in tests
- [ ] Components render efficiently
